# /api/* is served by the Cloudflare Worker in `apps/worker/` (v2).
#
# v2 architecture forbids a Render runtime dependency (see CLAUDE.md
# Non-Negotiable Rule 1 + docs/architecture/architecture-v2.md §7 +
# docs/architecture/frontend-routing.md "Worker base URL contract").
# The Worker is bound either:
#   (a) same-origin at the Pages zone (preferred; no rewrite needed), or
#   (b) on a dedicated subdomain exposed to the client via
#       `PUBLIC_WORKER_BASE_URL` at build time.
# Globe `fetch()` in `src/islands/GlobeApp.tsx` already reads
# `PUBLIC_WORKER_BASE_URL` — no Pages rewrite is required at runtime.
#
# DO NOT re-add a `/api/* → terrasight-api-o959.onrender.com` rewrite.
# The legacy Render maintenance stub (backend/main.py) is scheduled for
# removal once the Worker deploy is live.
